  "Initiated By" : "UNITED STATES SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION",
  "Allegations" : "SEC ADMIN RELEASE 34-72186, INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT OF 1940 RELEASE 31049, MAY 19, 2014:  THE SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (\"COMMISSION\") DEEMS IT APPROPRIATE AND IN THE PUBLIC INTEREST THAT PUBLIC ADMINISTRATIVE AND CEASE-AND-DESIST PROCEEDINGS BE, AND HEREBY ARE, INSTITUTED PURSUANT TO SECTIONS 15(B) AND 21C OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 (\"EXCHANGE ACT\"), AND SECTION 9(B) OF THE INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT OF 1940 (\"INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT\") AGAINST MICHAEL H. JOHNSON (\"JOHNSON\" OR \"RESPONDENT\").  THIS PROCEEDING ARISES OUT SECURITIES LENDING PRACTICES AT A REGISTERED BROKER-DEALER THAT RESULTED IN SYSTEMATIC VIOLATIONS OF RULE 204 OF REGULATION SHO. JOHNSON AND HIS SUBORDINATES IN THE SECURITIES LENDING DEPARTMENT IMPLEMENTED PROCEDURES THAT THEY KNEW, OR WERE RECKLESS IN NOT KNOWING, DID NOT COMPLY WITH RULE 204 OF REGULATION SHO. IN SO DOING, JOHNSON WILLFULLY AIDED AND ABETTED AND CAUSED THE BROKER-DEALER'S VIOLATIONS OF RULES 204(A) AND 204(B) OF REGULATION SHO, WHICH REQUIRE REGISTERED PARTICIPANTS OF CLEARING AGENCIES TO CLOSE OUT CONTINUOUS NET SETTLEMENT (\"CNS\") FAILURES TO DELIVER RESULTING FROM LONG SALES BY MARKET OPEN T+6, TO CLOSE OUT CNS FAILURES TO DELIVER RESULTING FROM SHORT SALES BY MARKET OPEN T+4, AND IMPOSE PRE-BORROWING RESTRICTIONS ON SECURITIES FOR WHICH THE CLOSE-OUT REQUIREMENTS ARE VIOLATED. IN ADDITION, JOHNSON FAILED REASONABLY TO SUPERVISE THE TWO VICE PRESIDENTS OF SECURITIES LENDING WITHIN THE MEANING OF SECTION 15(B)(4)(E) OF THE EXCHANGE ACT WITH A VIEW TO DETECT AND PREVENT THEM FROM WILLFULLY AIDING AND ABETTING CAUSED THE BROKER-DEALER'S VIOLATIONS OF RULE 204(A).",
